cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) for computer vision tasks such as human pose estimation and age estimation from face images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new loss function for the ConvNets, which makes it relevant to the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses publicly available datasets for human pose estimation, which makes it relevant to the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
